Job Description:
Project Management Advisors, Inc. is looking to hire a full-timeProject Coordinator position for our South San Francisco office location. The Project Coordinator is a highly-skilled organizer who coordinates people’s feedback, schedules, and assures timely processing and tracking of key deliverables while supporting the project management team. As a task manager, this position requires a professional with superb attention to detail who can work under minimal supervision while demonstrating proactive and reliable support. Great organizational skills, excellent communication, and good computer skills are required, as well as the ability to maintain professionalism in the face of deadlines and handle confidential information with discretion and trustworthiness. Interaction with both internal and external clients on project status and key deliverables are priorities for this role.

Experience and Education
At least 1 year of related work experience and aligned interests
Bachelor’s degree preferred but not mandatory; concentration in business, accounting or finance, engineering, architecture, or construction, desirable but not required
Computer proficient, including knowledge in the following programs: Microsoft Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Adobe Acrobat, and Outlook
Proficiency with cloud-based software including DocuSign, Salesforce, Gmail, Google Sheets, Docs and Slides
Skills and Qualifications
A motivated self-starter with a positive attitude and high level of personal integrity and business ethics who thrives in a collaborative team environment
Display strong interpersonal, verbal and written communication skills
Develop and maintain long-term relationships with clients and other construction related and business professionals
Demonstrate knowledge and understanding of project controls, project management, construction documentation and sequencing
Ability to multi-task and stay in front of project changes; stay abreast of project details and scope changes
Ability to produce quality work products in a fast-paced environment while taking changes in stride
Must be highly organized and reliable with excellent attention to detail
Operates with a high degree of integrity and has ability to maintain discretion regarding personnel and industry-related matters
General knowledge of project management processes, understands basics of Owner’s Rep/Developer industry
Duties and Responsibilities
Use templates to produce standard project correspondence and prepare emails for Project Team;
Create and maintain electronic and paper project files in accordance with filing procedures, including operation, maintenance and warranty documents and manuals;
Manage phones, calendars, and itineraries of Project Team;
Assist clients and vendors with questions or requests on behalf of Project Team;
Participate in proposals preparation and translate proposals into contracts by extracting pertinent information;
Review contracts in coordination with Legal and Project Managers. Process final contracts for execution and track approval progress;
Manage solicitation, short listing, selection, procurement, and contract administration of consultants, contractors, and vendors and ensure compliance with insurance requirements;
Manage the coordination between designers, builders and other team members on selected projects and programs;
Assist with or prepare budgets for projects and programs; budgets will include real estate, financing, soft costs, hard cost and equipment. Assist with preparation cash flow estimates and commitment schedules.
Prepare monthly draw packages, gather and review all relevant information from outside parties to generate reporting and correspondence. Deliver draw packages to the client and follow up on payables;
Schedule and organize meetings, conference calls and appointments. Prepare documents for meetings, including but not limited to creation and assembly of agendas, meeting decks, and documents for distribution and coordinate site visits. Track attendance and interact with attendees to address project or event questions and issues;
Attend team meetings; create and distribute meeting minutes and monitor follow-up of action items to completion; upload to project websites or file as appropriate;
Stay abreast of project details and scope changes; monitor and expedite the flow of information, such as requests for information and submittals;
Develop or assist with enhancement of Program and Project quality control and reporting systems. Focus will be placed on increasing levels of detail for Executive Summary to Detailed Analysis covering Status, Cost, Schedule, Open Items for the program projects;
Assists with closeout of the designer and builder’s contracts.
PMA operates from offices in Chicago (corporate), Los Angeles, San Diego, San Francisco and Orlando and has managed more than $5 billion in project value for a diverse range client and of projects, among them commercial, residential, institutional, life sciences, municipal, not-for-profit and educational assignments.

PMA recruits the best talent in the industry, but project management experience alone is not enough. We seek candidates who fit with our values, operating style and accountability commitment to our clients. In exchange, we provide staff with opportunities for professional growth and development with a highly competitive compensation and benefits package. When it comes to the best in project management talent, we’re proud to say,“we get it”.

Individuals looking to relocate to the South San Francisco area are encouraged to apply.

We are interested in every qualified candidate who is eligible to work in the United States. However, we are not able to offer sponsorship.
